00:29:33.005 --> 00:29:35.030
I agree with letting
go of the past

00:29:35.030 --> 00:29:36.710
and not looking to
the future, but I

00:29:36.710 --> 00:29:40.250
think it's harder to do if
there's actually something

00:29:40.250 --> 00:29:43.340
going on in the present that
doesn't deserve focus maybe

00:29:43.340 --> 00:29:44.530
or drags us down.

00:29:44.530 --> 00:29:45.207
What do we do?

00:29:45.207 --> 00:29:46.040
HAEMIN SUNIM: Right.

00:29:46.040 --> 00:29:48.020
Right.

00:29:48.020 --> 00:29:50.780
First of all, my
heart goes out to you.

00:29:50.780 --> 00:29:54.080
You'll be in a very difficult
situation, especially when

00:29:54.080 --> 00:29:55.460
your child is sick.

00:29:55.460 --> 00:29:58.280
It's a really daunting thing.

00:29:58.280 --> 00:30:00.545
Or you yourself has
some kind of illness.

00:30:04.360 --> 00:30:06.040
What I would say is this.

00:30:06.040 --> 00:30:13.000
If you are carefully examine
your body or examine your mind,

00:30:13.000 --> 00:30:18.790
you will notice that you
are not sick 24 hours.

00:30:18.790 --> 00:30:19.720
You know what I mean?

00:30:19.720 --> 00:30:24.190
Even if you are sick, even
if you have an illness,

00:30:24.190 --> 00:30:28.660
you are not sick 24 hours a day.

00:30:28.660 --> 00:30:31.480
But what's troubling
you is whenever

00:30:31.480 --> 00:30:35.380
you have a thought
of illness, whenever

00:30:35.380 --> 00:30:36.890
gosh I have an illness.

00:30:36.890 --> 00:30:38.440
I don't know what to do.

00:30:38.440 --> 00:30:41.980
Then that thought
triggers this depression

00:30:41.980 --> 00:30:44.650
or depressive emotions.

00:30:44.650 --> 00:30:48.430
So realize that when
you are little bit

00:30:48.430 --> 00:30:51.910
in a difficult
situation, maybe it

00:30:51.910 --> 00:30:55.660
is the thought that keep
thinking about it again

00:30:55.660 --> 00:30:58.480
and again that is
causing the problem.

00:30:58.480 --> 00:31:01.840
What-- but sometimes
we do forget,

00:31:01.840 --> 00:31:05.920
and then we watch TV and watch
some funny episode of sitcom

00:31:05.920 --> 00:31:11.290
or something then we can
laugh because our mind is not

00:31:11.290 --> 00:31:13.150
dwelling on that thought.

00:31:13.150 --> 00:31:20.781
So as the thought we momentarily
not dwelling on, then we

00:31:20.781 --> 00:31:21.280
don't--

00:31:21.280 --> 00:31:26.020
we can appreciate what is
happening in spite of this.

00:31:26.020 --> 00:31:30.610
For example, I remember I
was in a difficult situation

00:31:30.610 --> 00:31:38.980
where I had a fan in
Korea who really liked me

00:31:38.980 --> 00:31:43.630
obsessively and tried to
follow me around and show up

00:31:43.630 --> 00:31:48.310
on every single talk that I was
giving, and I was a little bit

00:31:48.310 --> 00:31:49.780
scared.

00:31:49.780 --> 00:31:53.440
This person was
almost stalker right.

00:31:53.440 --> 00:31:58.000
Whenever I thought about her,
I was feeling a little bit

00:31:58.000 --> 00:32:02.770
depressed because this
person is projecting

00:32:02.770 --> 00:32:05.810
a lot of this person's
emotion onto me.

00:32:05.810 --> 00:32:08.410
And if I do not tell--

00:32:08.410 --> 00:32:12.010
or satisfied this person's
needs, then this person

00:32:12.010 --> 00:32:16.000
goes online and ended up
saying all the negative things

00:32:16.000 --> 00:32:19.180
about me and then
making people believe

00:32:19.180 --> 00:32:21.970
this person's testimony.

00:32:21.970 --> 00:32:25.720
But whenever I was
thinking about her,

00:32:25.720 --> 00:32:28.900
I realized that my mind
became very depressed.

00:32:28.900 --> 00:32:32.500
However, when I was
not thinking about her,

00:32:32.500 --> 00:32:35.050
I realized that I was OK.

00:32:35.050 --> 00:32:39.520
So the very source of suffering
was a thought I realized.

00:32:39.520 --> 00:32:43.210
What is making us feel
really depressed and angry

00:32:43.210 --> 00:32:46.570
is whether we dwell
on that thought.

00:32:46.570 --> 00:32:49.870
So if we can just bring our
mind to present moment, what

00:32:49.870 --> 00:32:52.180
is really happening
right in front of us,

00:32:52.180 --> 00:32:55.240
you can have a cup of
tea with your best friend

00:32:55.240 --> 00:32:58.700
or you can be listening
to inspiring talk,

00:32:58.700 --> 00:33:03.820
then you don't have to think
about those kind of problems.

00:33:03.820 --> 00:33:05.090
You see what I mean.

00:33:05.090 --> 00:33:07.690
So I would say that
pay more attention

00:33:07.690 --> 00:33:10.712
to present moment even more.

00:33:10.712 --> 00:33:12.045
SHIFALI MUDUMBA: More questions?

00:33:12.045 --> 00:33:14.080
AUDIENCE: I have a
question on whether you

00:33:14.080 --> 00:33:15.600
have any suggestions--

00:33:15.600 --> 00:33:18.490
I know you've talked a lot
about individual practice

00:33:18.490 --> 00:33:21.820
to be more present
and more aware.

00:33:21.820 --> 00:33:25.630
As a family with children
and with your partner,

00:33:25.630 --> 00:33:27.310
is there any practices
that you think

00:33:27.310 --> 00:33:31.152
could help as a family--
the whole family?

00:33:31.152 --> 00:33:36.050
HAEMIN SUNIM: When you are
living with many children

00:33:36.050 --> 00:33:38.380
then you have a
very demanding job

00:33:38.380 --> 00:33:41.650
and when you go back you have
a partner waiting for you,

00:33:41.650 --> 00:33:45.500
then it's very difficult for
us to have a sense of calmness

00:33:45.500 --> 00:33:47.780
in everyday activity.

00:33:47.780 --> 00:33:53.230
So what I usually suggest is
see if you can still carve out

00:33:53.230 --> 00:33:56.080
a little bit of time even
if it's five minutes a day

00:33:56.080 --> 00:33:57.560
or 10 minutes a day.

00:33:57.560 --> 00:34:01.720
So what that means is
rather than getting off

00:34:01.720 --> 00:34:05.480
at your regular bus stations,
you can get off like a three

00:34:05.480 --> 00:34:08.170
stop before, and
then you can maybe

00:34:08.170 --> 00:34:11.770
enjoy you know walking
back home while listening

00:34:11.770 --> 00:34:12.790
to your favorite song.

00:34:12.790 --> 00:34:18.190
So carving out-- just having
this intention to care about

00:34:18.190 --> 00:34:22.300
myself first, you can go to
your favorite coffee shop

00:34:22.300 --> 00:34:26.410
and while you are
enjoying coffee or tea,

00:34:26.410 --> 00:34:29.300
you can have a more
relaxed time and checking

00:34:29.300 --> 00:34:32.139
in with my mind and my body.

00:34:32.139 --> 00:34:34.239
Or you can go to your
favorite bookshop.

00:34:34.239 --> 00:34:37.060
Whenever I go to bookshop
and see a empty chair,

00:34:37.060 --> 00:34:38.695
I'm so happy.

00:34:38.695 --> 00:34:42.909
I go sit there and read, and
this gives me a downtime.

00:34:42.909 --> 00:34:45.520
And then when I go to--

00:34:45.520 --> 00:34:49.280
back to your home or
go back to your work,

00:34:49.280 --> 00:34:52.870
then you can go back
with your refreshed mind.

00:34:52.870 --> 00:34:58.600
And also in your daily activity
with your family member, what

00:34:58.600 --> 00:35:02.200
I would suggest is rather
than thinking that we already

00:35:02.200 --> 00:35:05.410
know about our family
member, we often

00:35:05.410 --> 00:35:07.780
think that I already
know everything

00:35:07.780 --> 00:35:10.965
there is to know about my
boyfriend, girlfriend, husband,

00:35:10.965 --> 00:35:13.840
and wife or my children,
then what happen

00:35:13.840 --> 00:35:16.960
is we stop asking questions.

00:35:16.960 --> 00:35:21.550
We are not curious about
what happened to their lives.

00:35:21.550 --> 00:35:24.100
But the thing is
we always change.

00:35:24.100 --> 00:35:26.140
We are changing.

00:35:26.140 --> 00:35:28.540
Our children are changing.

00:35:28.540 --> 00:35:31.130
Our husband or
partners are changing.

00:35:31.130 --> 00:35:36.850
So if we approach to your family
member with sense of curiosity

00:35:36.850 --> 00:35:40.330
and humility that you don't know
everything there is to know,

00:35:40.330 --> 00:35:42.580
then you can have a
deeper conversation.

00:35:42.580 --> 00:35:45.520
You can ask, oh, how
have you been today?

00:35:45.520 --> 00:35:47.930
How was-- what is going on?

00:35:47.930 --> 00:35:51.820
And then it is also important
to share not just the fact.

00:35:51.820 --> 00:35:54.500
People often just say, oh what
time are you getting home?

00:35:54.500 --> 00:35:55.570
Oh, 7:00.

00:35:55.570 --> 00:35:56.800
What did you have dinner?

00:35:56.800 --> 00:35:58.780
I had chicken teriyaki.

00:35:58.780 --> 00:35:59.840
That's like a fact.

00:35:59.840 --> 00:36:00.940
You just asked.

00:36:00.940 --> 00:36:04.360
However, I think it is
important that we also

00:36:04.360 --> 00:36:09.100
ask how we are feeling,
which is the deeper self.

00:36:09.100 --> 00:36:10.630
How are you feeling?

00:36:10.630 --> 00:36:17.090
So allowing some time for
us to unpack our own feeling

00:36:17.090 --> 00:36:20.230
and feeling that the other
person is really hearing me

00:36:20.230 --> 00:36:22.765
out, it can create deeper bond.

00:36:22.765 --> 00:36:24.070
AUDIENCE: Hello.

00:36:24.070 --> 00:36:26.810
Thank you for being here today.

00:36:26.810 --> 00:36:31.390
There's a situation that I
find puzzling in general,

00:36:31.390 --> 00:36:34.450
which is on one hand the--

00:36:34.450 --> 00:36:37.240
I buy into the power
of vulnerability,

00:36:37.240 --> 00:36:40.750
the importance of
embracing imperfections,

00:36:40.750 --> 00:36:42.350
of knowing them, et cetera.

00:36:42.350 --> 00:36:44.140
But on the other hand,
I have the feeling

00:36:44.140 --> 00:36:48.550
that the world and
especially social media world

00:36:48.550 --> 00:36:50.890
can be a great
medium for knowledge,

00:36:50.890 --> 00:36:53.770
et cetera, there is this
race towards perfection

00:36:53.770 --> 00:36:57.520
and only actually
depicting what's perfect.

00:36:57.520 --> 00:36:59.840
When you look at people
today on social media,

00:36:59.840 --> 00:37:03.629
no one really puts their picture
when they're feeling ill or bad

00:37:03.629 --> 00:37:05.420
or when they're arguing
with their partner.

00:37:05.420 --> 00:37:08.890
It's all like how
happy, clappy, peppy.

00:37:08.890 --> 00:37:13.390
And I find it really puzzling
because I think it's antinomic.

00:37:13.390 --> 00:37:15.460
What would be your
advice to maybe,

00:37:15.460 --> 00:37:17.950
especially the
younger ones that are

00:37:17.950 --> 00:37:21.880
going to experience more and
more social pressure on media

00:37:21.880 --> 00:37:26.260
and to still keep that
philosophy of loving

00:37:26.260 --> 00:37:27.870
imperfections?

00:37:27.870 --> 00:37:30.490
Thank you.

00:37:30.490 --> 00:37:34.390
HAEMIN SUNIM: I was in
Canada near Vancouver.

00:37:34.390 --> 00:37:36.550
I was invited to
give a talk there.

00:37:36.550 --> 00:37:42.070
And then after the event,
I drove up with my friend,

00:37:42.070 --> 00:37:44.440
and I heard there's
a beautiful mountain.

00:37:44.440 --> 00:37:47.180
And if you just walk
about four hours,

00:37:47.180 --> 00:37:51.160
and you'll see snow-capped
mountain with beautiful lake.

00:37:51.160 --> 00:37:53.410
So I decided to go there.

00:37:53.410 --> 00:37:56.080
So I went there,
but what I did not

00:37:56.080 --> 00:37:59.690
know was that while
climbing up going up,

00:37:59.690 --> 00:38:02.830
up up, there were
a lot of flies.

00:38:02.830 --> 00:38:05.020
You know the box flies?

00:38:05.020 --> 00:38:08.400
And so for the last four hours,
as I was growing up, I would--

00:38:08.400 --> 00:38:09.290
I have to do this.

00:38:09.290 --> 00:38:11.920
I have to do this constantly
because there are so

00:38:11.920 --> 00:38:14.810
many flies and bugs around me.

00:38:14.810 --> 00:38:18.520
And then once I get to that
in a beautiful scenic spot,

00:38:18.520 --> 00:38:20.470
I was very happy,
but at the same time

00:38:20.470 --> 00:38:24.750
I was extremely
hungry and exhausted.

00:38:24.750 --> 00:38:26.950
However, when I
took the photo, I

00:38:26.950 --> 00:38:33.310
was smiling as if
you know there was

00:38:33.310 --> 00:38:36.970
no bug, as if there was
no exhaustion, as if there

00:38:36.970 --> 00:38:38.620
was no hunger.

00:38:38.620 --> 00:38:46.270
So when you see very happy face
on your friend's Facebook entry

00:38:46.270 --> 00:38:50.410
or Twitter or
other social media,

00:38:50.410 --> 00:38:54.490
Instagram or YouTube,
just remind yourself

00:38:54.490 --> 00:38:57.490
that maybe this person
was fighting off

00:38:57.490 --> 00:39:00.330
the flies for the
last four hours

00:39:00.330 --> 00:39:04.180
and then suffering from
the exhaustion and hunger.

00:39:04.180 --> 00:39:13.180
So I think having that
awareness helps quite a bit.

00:39:13.180 --> 00:39:16.120
And also rather than
comparing ourselves

00:39:16.120 --> 00:39:18.490
with somebody who's doing
a lot better because there

00:39:18.490 --> 00:39:24.010
will be always somebody who is
always doing better than you--

00:39:24.010 --> 00:39:25.090
I was advised--

00:39:25.090 --> 00:39:29.320
I remember we have to compare
ourselves to our old us.

00:39:29.320 --> 00:39:33.940
So, for example, I remember
in Korea, the richest person

00:39:33.940 --> 00:39:38.560
in Korea is the owner of Samsung
you know the Samsung right?

00:39:38.560 --> 00:39:42.220
And so I thought that, wow,
this guy must be really rich.

00:39:42.220 --> 00:39:46.150
And then one day I was
reading a newspaper article,

00:39:46.150 --> 00:39:50.560
and it ranked the wealth of
different people in the world.

00:39:50.560 --> 00:39:53.740
And he ranked like
170-something.

00:39:53.740 --> 00:39:59.180
And then I realized that even
if he was to comparing himself,

00:39:59.180 --> 00:40:03.880
then he would feel, oh, gosh,
I only made it 170-something.

00:40:03.880 --> 00:40:05.950
You see what I mean?

00:40:05.950 --> 00:40:07.810
So we shouldn't do that.

00:40:07.810 --> 00:40:13.690
Rather we should become proud
of how much we have achieved

00:40:13.690 --> 00:40:17.380
so far for the last
10 years or 15 years,

00:40:17.380 --> 00:40:21.350
how much we have grown
spiritually, emotionally,

00:40:21.350 --> 00:40:23.650
and also career-wise.

00:40:23.650 --> 00:40:26.125
SHIFALI MUDUMBA: I think
we'll take one last question.

00:40:26.125 --> 00:40:27.000
AUDIENCE: Right here.

00:40:27.000 --> 00:40:28.124
SHIFALI MUDUMBA: Oh, sorry.

00:40:28.124 --> 00:40:29.341
Yes.

00:40:29.341 --> 00:40:32.170
AUDIENCE: I think we can learn
a lot definitely and apply

00:40:32.170 --> 00:40:33.750
a lot to our lives.

00:40:33.750 --> 00:40:37.630
I am just thinking if we take
this idea of being content

00:40:37.630 --> 00:40:40.130
and being constantly
present in our--

00:40:40.130 --> 00:40:43.240
to the extreme and let's say
everyone became like a Buddhist

00:40:43.240 --> 00:40:47.920
monk or close to that,
what would happen?

00:40:47.920 --> 00:40:51.100
Because a lot of the stuff that
we do is because the problems

00:40:51.100 --> 00:40:53.170
we have, the things
that bugs us,

00:40:53.170 --> 00:40:56.630
the ambitions and
insecurities that drives us.

00:40:56.630 --> 00:40:59.360
So how do you view being
content with ourselves

00:40:59.360 --> 00:41:03.400
and really enjoying the
life versus our obligation

00:41:03.400 --> 00:41:07.750
towards society or
civilization to progress it

00:41:07.750 --> 00:41:13.150
by constantly seeing the bugs
and trying to get rid of them

00:41:13.150 --> 00:41:16.480
or put them aside or make
them not bite you right

00:41:16.480 --> 00:41:19.312
rather than being content
that they are around you

00:41:19.312 --> 00:41:20.270
and just ignoring them?

00:41:23.300 --> 00:41:26.860
HAEMIN SUNIM: Like connecting
to the present moment

00:41:26.860 --> 00:41:29.480
and being mindful
of what's going on,

00:41:29.480 --> 00:41:32.290
it doesn't mean that
you become lazy.

00:41:32.290 --> 00:41:35.140
It doesn't become-- it
doesn't mean that you become

00:41:35.140 --> 00:41:37.450
I don't care about the world.

00:41:37.450 --> 00:41:41.470
I think just being
content actually

00:41:41.470 --> 00:41:48.640
allows us to engage in our
work in a much proficient way.

00:41:48.640 --> 00:41:52.240
When you are happy, notice
that you can actually

00:41:52.240 --> 00:41:54.460
respond quickly.

00:41:54.460 --> 00:41:59.230
There is a space for you
to tolerate annoyances

00:41:59.230 --> 00:42:05.170
of other people because you find
much more peaceful at heart.

00:42:05.170 --> 00:42:07.660
The opposite is the problem.

00:42:07.660 --> 00:42:11.470
That is if your heart is closed
off and feeling that you're

00:42:11.470 --> 00:42:13.930
completely isolated
and you are thinking

00:42:13.930 --> 00:42:18.430
about what happened in the past
while ignoring the bug that

00:42:18.430 --> 00:42:24.190
is coming up right now, then I
think this can become problems.

00:42:24.190 --> 00:42:28.180
Your stress level is already
up and feeling like a victim

00:42:28.180 --> 00:42:30.960
because I have another
wok that I have to do.

00:42:30.960 --> 00:42:34.870
So I would say that
just being mindful

00:42:34.870 --> 00:42:41.050
doesn't mean that you
become like a corpse.

00:42:41.050 --> 00:42:45.520
Instead you can actually respond
much more compassionately,

00:42:45.520 --> 00:42:50.080
much quickly to the demands
or difficulty of other peoples

00:42:50.080 --> 00:42:51.586
having.

00:42:51.586 --> 00:42:54.765
SHIFALI MUDUMBA: One last
question in the back, Dennis.

00:42:54.765 --> 00:42:57.820
AUDIENCE: Thank
you for being here.

00:42:57.820 --> 00:43:00.600
So we have a mindfulness
meditation community here

00:43:00.600 --> 00:43:01.222
at Google.

00:43:01.222 --> 00:43:02.680
And there's a lot
of people who are

00:43:02.680 --> 00:43:04.480
I think trying to get
into a daily practice.

00:43:04.480 --> 00:43:05.896
I'm really curious
to hear what is

00:43:05.896 --> 00:43:09.010
your take on the benefits
of a daily practice

00:43:09.010 --> 00:43:10.520
and also maybe
some practical tips

00:43:10.520 --> 00:43:12.310
around how to
establish one because I

00:43:12.310 --> 00:43:13.960
think it's quite hard
in the beginning.

00:43:13.960 --> 00:43:15.460
It takes a while
to get the benefits

00:43:15.460 --> 00:43:18.080
or to start feeling the impact.

00:43:18.080 --> 00:43:21.747
So if you've any tips on how to
best get into that a routine.

00:43:21.747 --> 00:43:22.580
HAEMIN SUNIM: Right.

00:43:22.580 --> 00:43:24.700
Right.

00:43:24.700 --> 00:43:27.820
Well, I would say
that if you are

00:43:27.820 --> 00:43:29.560
interested in
mindfulness meditation

00:43:29.560 --> 00:43:31.990
and you want to
get into that but I

00:43:31.990 --> 00:43:35.740
don't know how to do that, then
the first thing I would say

00:43:35.740 --> 00:43:37.780
is make a--

00:43:37.780 --> 00:43:40.570
have a very low expectation.

00:43:40.570 --> 00:43:42.840
So rather than
say, oh, I'm going

00:43:42.840 --> 00:43:46.330
to sit quietly for the next 20
minutes without any thinking

00:43:46.330 --> 00:43:51.670
and then paying attention fully
to my breath, just reduce.

00:43:51.670 --> 00:43:54.020
Scale back and say
that well I'm going

00:43:54.020 --> 00:43:55.480
to spend next two minutes.

00:43:55.480 --> 00:43:56.840
See if we can--

00:43:56.840 --> 00:44:01.540
if I can just sit quietly
and enjoy my breath.

00:44:01.540 --> 00:44:04.550
And if you accomplish two
minutes, then you can say,

00:44:04.550 --> 00:44:07.060
oh, I will do 2
minutes and 30 seconds,

00:44:07.060 --> 00:44:09.400
and then slowly you
can increase it.

00:44:09.400 --> 00:44:14.700
So you don't have to say I'm
going to somehow bliss out.

